{"type":"message","id":"4a931ecb","parentId":"229d351c","timestamp":"2026-03-12T23:15:31.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user's crontab is empty, the script exists but there's no system cron entry. So the daily ping is not running at all - the OpenClaw job is disabled and there's no system cron replacing it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"That's the problem. Here's the situation:\n\n1. **OpenClaw cron job** (`daily-ping-telegram`) — **disabled**, last error says it was \"replaced with system cron\"\n2. **System crontab** — **empty**. No daily ping entry exists there either\n3. **The script exists** at `/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh` but nothing is calling it\n\nSo the daily ping is dead in the water — disabled in OpenClaw and never actually set up in system cron. Looks like someone disabled it with the intent to migrate to system cron but never finished the setup.\n\n**Want me to re-enable the OpenClaw cron job so it fires again at 7am?** Or would you prefer I set it up as a system cron instead?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":28711,"output":267,"cacheRead":512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29490,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773357322834}}
{"type":"message","id":"a12d25e7","parentId":"4a931ecb","timestamp":"2026-03-12T23:20:46.497Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-13 07:20 GMT+8] check that the script can run properly by manually triggering it. last reply from you on this matters: Looking at the existing scripts and the recurring timeout issues, here's my honest assessment:\n\nCurrent Problems\n\nThe agentTurn approach is fundamentally misaligned with what you're trying to do:\n\n1. Spawning overhead — Agent startup + model loading eats 30-60 seconds before any work happens\n2. yfinance delays — Stock fetching can take 2-5 minutes, which eats into the 5-minute timeout window\n3. Model fallback confusion — The error shows xai/grok-4-1-fast-reasoning which isn't even in your config (should be NVIDIA-only)\n4. Overengineering — You're asking an LLM to do what a 20-line Python script already does better\n\nBetter Strategy\n\nUse the existing infrastructure (daily-ping-cron.sh + Python scripts) instead of agentTurn:\n\nOption A: Fix the Shell Script Approach (Recommended)\n\nUpdate /home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh to:\n\n1. Fetch all data (Bitcoin via curl, stocks via yfinance, GitHub trending via API)\n2. Format the message locally (no LLM needed)\n3. Send directly via Telegram API or OpenClaw CLI\n\nPros:\n\n• Runs in 30-60 seconds total\n• No agent spawning overhead\n• Stock data already available via yfinance in the existing script\n• Predictable timing\n\nCons:\n\n• None, really\n\nOption B: Hybrid Approach\n\nKeep the cron job simple:\n\nshell\n\n# System cron (not OpenClaw agent)\n0 7 * * * /home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh && /usr/bin/python3 /home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-sender.py --send\nThe shell script already:\n\n• Fetches Bitcoin ✓\n• Fetches stocks via yfinance ✓\n• Logs everything to structured files ✓\n\nThe Python sender just needs to:\n\n• Parse the log files (already does this)\n• Format with your preferred emoji/delta format (needs update)\n• Send via Telegram (already does this)\n\nOption C: What You're Doing Now (Broken)\n\nAgentTurn that:\n\n• Spawns an agent (30s)\n• Loads model context (30s)\n• Runs yfinance (2-5 min)\n• Hits 5-min timeout ❌\n\nMy Recommendation\n\nDisable the OpenClaw cron job, switch to system cron calling the existing scripts, and I can help update the Python formatter to use your preferred format with:\n\n• 📈📉 delta indicators\n• 24h change percentages\n• Top 10 trending repos (not just top stars)\n• Proper K-formatting for stars\n\nSimple, fast, reliable.\n\nWant me to:\n\n1. Update daily-ping-cron.sh to fetch top 10 trending repos (created recently with high star velocity)?\n2. Update daily-ping-sender.py with your preferred format?\n3. Set up a system cron job instead of OpenClaw agentTurn?"}],"timestamp":1773357646493}}
{"type":"message","id":"603ff62a","parentId":"a12d25e7","timestamp":"2026-03-12T23:20:55.915Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to manually trigger the daily ping script to see if it runs properly. Let me first look at the existing scripts to understand what they do, then run them.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the existing scripts and try running them."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"9200af08-c26f-42e4-b6ee-a81a6d6552d6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"67962268-30d7-4393-a54c-392e0f911a5d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-sender.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":25686,"output":151,"cacheRead":4416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30253,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773357646495}}
{"type":"message","id":"213db0d3","parentId":"603ff62a","timestamp":"2026-03-12T23:20:55.949Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"9200af08-c26f-42e4-b6ee-a81a6d6552d6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Daily Ping Cron Job v2.0\n# Executes at 7:00 AM SGT (23:00 UTC)\n# Fixed: Better error handling, PATH setup for cron, explicit logging\n\n# Set PATH for cron environment\nexport PATH=\"/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Log file setup\nLOG_DIR=\"/home/project/openclaw/logs\"\nLOG_FILE=\"$LOG_DIR/daily-ping-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log\"\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\nif ! mkdir -p \"$LOG_DIR\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Cannot create log directory $LOG_DIR\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Check if we can write to log file\nif ! touch \"$LOG_FILE\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Cannot write to log file $LOG_FILE\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Function to log with timestamp\nlog() {\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')] $1\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n}\n\nlog \"Starting daily ping job...\"\nlog \"Log file: $LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Fetch Bitcoin price from CoinGecko\nlog \"Fetching Bitcoin data from CoinGecko...\"\nBTC_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true\" 2>&1)\nCURL_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: Bitcoin fetch failed (curl exit: $CURL_EXIT)\"\n    log \"Curl output: $BTC_DATA\"\nelse\n    BTC_PRICE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd\":[0-9]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n    BTC_CHANGE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd_24h_change\":[-0-9.]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n    \n    if [ -z \"$BTC_PRICE\" ]; then\n        log \"ERROR: Could not parse Bitcoin price from response\"\n        log \"Response: $BTC_DATA\"\n    else\n        log \"Bitcoin: $BTC_PRICE (change: $BTC_CHANGE%)\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Fetch top GitHub repos\nlog \"Fetching GitHub data...\"\nGH_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=created:>2024-01-01&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=10\" 2>&1)\nCURL_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: GitHub fetch failed (curl exit: $CURL_EXIT)\"\nelse\n    # Verify we got valid JSON\n    if echo \"$GH_DATA\" | grep -q '\"total_count\":'; then\n        log \"GitHub data fetched successfully\"\n    else\n        log \"ERROR: GitHub response invalid\"\n        log \"Response preview: $(echo \"$GH_DATA\" | head -c 200)\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Fetch stock data using uv run (more reliable than source activate)\nlog \"Fetching stock data (NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD)...\"\n\n# Use uv run from the correct directory\ncd /home/project/openclaw || exit 1\n\nSTOCK_OUTPUT=$(uv run python3 << 'PYTHON_SCRIPT'\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\nimport sys\n\ntickers = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresults = {}\n\ntry:\n    for symbol in tickers:\n        try:\n            t = yf.Ticker(symbol)\n            info = t.info\n            current_price = info.get('currentPrice') or info.get('regularMarketPrice', 0)\n            prev_close = info.get('previousClose', 0)\n            change_pct = info.get('regularMarketChangePercent')\n            if change_pct is None and prev_close > 0:\n                change_pct = ((current_price - prev_close) / prev_close) * 100\n            results[symbol] = {\n                'price': current_price,\n                'change_pct': change_pct or 0,\n                'company': info.get('shortName', symbol)\n            }\n        except Exception as e:\n            results[symbol] = {'error': str(e)}\n    \n    print(json.dumps(results))\n    sys.exit(0)\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(json.dumps({'error': str(e)}))\n    sys.exit(1)\nPYTHON_SCRIPT\n2>&1)\n\nPYTHON_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $PYTHON_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: Stock data fetch failed (python exit: $PYTHON_EXIT)\"\n    log \"Python output: $STOCK_OUTPUT\"\nelse\n    echo \"$STOCK_OUTPUT\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n    log \"Stock data fetched successfully\"\nfi\n\nlog \"Daily ping job completed\"\n\n# Return appropriate exit code\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ] || [ $PYTHON_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    exit 1\nelse\n    exit 0\nfi\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773357655947}}
{"type":"message","id":"1feb389b","parentId":"213db0d3","timestamp":"2026-03-12T23:20:55.978Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"67962268-30d7-4393-a54c-392e0f911a5d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDaily Ping Message Sender\nReads data from cron job logs and sends formatted message via Telegram\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\n\ndef read_log_file():\n    \"\"\"Read today's log file\"\"\"\n    today = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    log_file = f\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/daily-ping-{today}.log\"\n    \n    try:\n        with open(log_file, 'r') as f:\n            return f.read()\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        return None\n\ndef parse_bitcoin_data(log_content):\n    \"\"\"Extract Bitcoin price and change from log\"\"\"\n    match = re.search(r'Bitcoin: (\\d+) \\(change: ([-\\d.]+)%\\)', log_content)\n    if match:\n        return {\n            'price': int(match.group(1)),\n            'change': float(match.group(2))\n        }\n    return None\n\ndef parse_stock_data(log_content):\n    \"\"\"Extract stock data from log\"\"\"\n    # Look for JSON block in log\n    json_match = re.search(r'\\{[^{}]*\"NVDA\"[^{}]*\\}', log_content, re.DOTALL)\n    if json_match:\n        try:\n            return json.loads(json_match.group())\n        except:\n            pass\n    return None\n\ndef format_message(bitcoin, stocks):\n    \"\"\"Format the daily ping message\"\"\"\n    date_str = datetime.now().strftime(\"%A, %B %d, %Y\")\n    \n    # Bitcoin section\n    btc_emoji = \"🔻\" if bitcoin['change'] < 0 else \"🟢\"\n    btc_alert = \"⚠️ ALERT: Drop > 10%!\" if bitcoin['change'] < -10 else \"✅ No alert\"\n    \n    message = f\"\"\"📅 **Daily Ping — {date_str}**\n\n💰 **Bitcoin Price**\n• Current: **${bitcoin['price']:,} USD**\n• 24h Change: **{bitcoin['change']:+.2f}%** {btc_emoji}\n• Status: {btc_alert}\n\n📊 **Tech Stocks (24h Change)**\n\n\"\"\"\n    \n    # Stock table\n    if stocks:\n        for symbol, data in stocks.items():\n            if 'error' not in data:\n                emoji = \"🔴\" if data['change_pct'] < 0 else \"🟢\"\n                company = data.get('company', symbol)\n                message += f\"• **{company}** ({symbol}): ${data['price']:.2f} ({data['change_pct']:+.2f}%) {emoji}\\n\"\n        \n        # Market summary\n        down_count = sum(1 for s in stocks.values() if 'error' not in s and s['change_pct'] < 0)\n        total_count = sum(1 for s in stocks.values() if 'error' not in s)\n        \n        message += f\"\\n📈 **Market Summary:** {down_count} of {total_count} stocks down\"\n        \n        # Find biggest loser\n        biggest_loser = None\n        biggest_drop = 0\n        for symbol, data in stocks.items():\n            if 'error' not in data and data['change_pct'] < biggest_drop:\n                biggest_drop = data['change_pct']\n                biggest_loser = symbol\n        \n        if biggest_loser:\n            message += f\" | 🔥 **{biggest_loser}** hit hardest at {biggest_drop:.2f}%\"\n    \n    message += \"\"\"\n\n🚀 **GitHub Top Repositories**\n✅ Top 5 trending repositories fetched\n\n---\n*Have a productive day!* 🤝\n\"\"\"\n    \n    return message\n\ndef send_telegram_message(message):\n    \"\"\"Send message via Telegram using OpenClaw\"\"\"\n    # Use OpenClaw CLI to send message\n    cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\", \"message\", \"send\",\n        \"--target\", \"1087368827\",\n        \"--channel\", \"telegram\",\n        \"--text\", message\n    ]\n    \n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True)\n        return result.returncode == 0\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error sending message: {e}\")\n        return False\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Main function\"\"\"\n    log_content = read_log_file()\n    \n    if not log_content:\n        print(\"Error: No log file found for today\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    bitcoin = parse_bitcoin_data(log_content)\n    stocks = parse_stock_data(log_content)\n    \n    if not bitcoin:\n        print(\"Error: Could not parse Bitcoin data\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    message = format_message(bitcoin, stocks)\n    \n    # Save formatted message for debugging\n    today = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    with open(f\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/message-{today}.txt\", 'w') as f:\n        f.write(message)\n    \n    print(\"Formatted message:\")\n    print(message)\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*50)\n    print(\"To send via Telegram, run with --send flag\")\n    \n    if \"--send\" in sys.argv:\n        if send_telegram_message(message):\n            print(\"✅ Message sent successfully!\")\n        else:\n            print(\"❌ Failed to send message\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773357655971}}
