{"type":"message","id":"153a0733","parentId":"94d16387","timestamp":"2026-03-12T23:26:35.002Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"1620ae3c-6324-4c6b-9c27-4fe17062b94a","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.11 (29dc654) — No $999 stand required.\n\nUsage: openclaw message send [options]\n\nSend a message\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id (accountId)\n  --buttons <json>       Telegram inline keyboard buttons as JSON (array of\n                         button rows)\n  --card <json>          Adaptive Card JSON object (when supported by the\n                         channel)\n  --channel <channel>    Channel:\n                         telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n  --components <json>    Discord components payload as JSON\n  --dry-run              Print payload and skip sending (default: false)\n  --gif-playback         Treat video media as GIF playback (WhatsApp only).\n                         (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>   Message body (required unless --media is set)\n  --media <path-or-url>  Attach media (image/audio/video/document). Accepts\n                         local paths or URLs.\n  --reply-to <id>        Reply-to message id\n  --silent               Send message silently without notification (Telegram +\n                         Discord) (default: false)\n  -t, --target <dest>    Recipient/channel: E.164 for WhatsApp/Signal, Telegram\n                         chat id/@username, Discord/Slack channel/user, or\n                         iMessage handle/chat_id"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2892,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.11 (29dc654) — No $999 stand required.\n\nUsage: openclaw message send [options]\n\nSend a message\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id (accountId)\n  --buttons <json>       Telegram inline keyboard buttons as JSON (array of\n                         button rows)\n  --card <json>          Adaptive Card JSON object (when supported by the\n                         channel)\n  --channel <channel>    Channel:\n                         telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n  --components <json>    Discord components payload as JSON\n  --dry-run              Print payload and skip sending (default: false)\n  --gif-playback         Treat video media as GIF playback (WhatsApp only).\n                         (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>   Message body (required unless --media is set)\n  --media <path-or-url>  Attach media (image/audio/video/document). Accepts\n                         local paths or URLs.\n  --reply-to <id>        Reply-to message id\n  --silent               Send message silently without notification (Telegram +\n                         Discord) (default: false)\n  -t, --target <dest>    Recipient/channel: E.164 for WhatsApp/Signal, Telegram\n                         chat id/@username, Discord/Slack channel/user, or\n                         iMessage handle/chat_id","cwd":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773357994997}}
