ey patterns\n+463 - `hardcoded_secret`: Entropy >=4.5 + length >=20\n+464 - `file_deletion`: shutil.rmtree, rm -rf, wildcard os.remove\n+465 - `credential_access`: SSH key access, password/token file access\n+466 - `sensitive_file_access`: .openclaw/config.json, MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, .bashrc, ~/.ssh/\n+467 \n+468 **YELLOW - MEDIUM (manual review):**\n+469 - `network_request`: requests, urllib, httpx, aiohttp\n+470 - `data_download`: urllib.urlretrieve, streaming downloads, wget, curl -O\n+471 - `file_access_outside_workspace`: /etc/, /sys/, home directory access\n+472 - `obfuscation`: base64 decode, ROT13, zlib/gzip compression\n+473 - `dynamic_import`: __import__(), importlib, exec(), compile()\n+474 - `api_key_usage`: API key assignments, AI service API references\n+475 - `environment_access`: os.environ, os.getenv, dotenv\n+476 \n+477 **GREEN - LOW (document & proceed):**\n+478 - `shell_command`: os.system (static string), subprocess, os.popen\n+479 - `file_operation`: open(), os.path.*, pathlib, shutil\n+480 - `json_parsing`: json.loads, json.load\n+481 - `yaml_parsing`: yaml.*, pyyaml\n+482 \n+483 ### v3.1 Key Enhancements (99% FP reduction)\n+484 - NPM integrity hash whitelist: skips sha512-xxx patterns in lock files\n+485 - Smart data flow: uploads (HIGH) vs downloads (MEDIUM)\n+486 - Context-aware docs: recognizes placeholders (your_api_key_here, sk-..., i18n patterns)\n+487 - Test file exclusions: test_*.py, conftest.py automatically skipped\n+488 - Lock file exclusions: NPM/pnpm/yarn/composer/poetry/Cargo/Gemfile skipped\n+489 \n 436 ### Usage Commands\n 437 ```bash\n-438 # Basic scan\n 439 cd /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/trustskill\n 440 source /opt/venv/bin/activate\n+494 \n+495 # Basic scan (standard mode)\n 441 python src/cli.py /path/to/skill\n 442 \n 443 # Deep scan with JSON output\n 444 python src/cli.py /path/to/skill --mode deep --format json\n 445 \n 446 # Export for manual review\n 447 python src/cli.py /path/to/skill --export-for-llm\n 448 \n-449 # Batch scan all workspace scripts\n+504 # Batch scan workspace scripts\n 450 python src/cli.py /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/scripts --mode deep --format json\n+506 \n+507 # Fast scan for quick triage\n+508 python src/cli.py /path/to/skill --mode fast\n 451 ```\n 452 \n+511 **Exit Codes:** 0 = safe/no HIGH risk, 1 = HIGH risk detected\n+512 **Test Suite:** 218 tests across 17 test files\n+513 \n 453 ### Workspace Scan Results (2026-02-22)\n-454 **Scanned:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/` (3 files)\n+515 Scanned: `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/` — 0 HIGH, 0 MEDIUM, 6 LOW -> SAFE\n 455 \n-456 | Risk Level | Count | Status |\n-457 |------------|-------|--------|\n-458 | 🔴 HIGH | 0 | ✅ None found |\n-459 | 🟡 MEDIUM | 0 | ✅ None found |\n-460 | 🟢 LOW | 6 | JSON parsing, file operations (normal) |\n-461 | ℹ️ INFO | 0 | - |\n-462 \n-463 **Assessment:** ✅ **SAFE** - No significant security issues in workspace scripts.\n-464 \n-465 **Findings Summary:**\n-466 - `daily-ping-cron.sh`: 2 LOW (JSON parsing for GitHub/stock data)\n-467 - `skill-search.py`: 4 LOW (file operations for catalog reading)\n-468 - All findings are standard operations (read-only file access, JSON parsing)\n-469 - No command injection, hardcoded secrets, or data exfiltration detected\n-470 \n-471 ### Security Categories Detected\n-472 | Category | Severity | Description |\n-473 |----------|----------|-------------|\n-474 | `command_injection` | HIGH | User input to eval/exec/os.system |\n-475 | `data_upload` | HIGH | POST/PUT to external servers |\n-476 | `hardcoded_secret` | HIGH | Real API keys/passwords |\n-477 | `data_download` | MEDIUM | File downloads from internet |\n-478 | `api_key_usage` | MEDIUM | API key references (usually placeholders) |\n-479 | `network_request` | MEDIUM | HTTP requests |\n-480 | `vulnerable_dependency` | MEDIUM | CVE in dependencies |\n-481 | `environment_access` | LOW | Reading env variables (normal) |\n-482 | `file_operation` | LOW | Standard file I/O |\n-483 \n-484 ### Red Flags (Immediate Action Required)\n-485 🚨 **STOP and investigate if found:**\n-486 1. Data exfiltration to unknown servers\n-487 2. Hidden network listeners/backdoors\n-488 3. Destructive operations (rm -rf /, shutil.rmtree on user dirs)\n-489 4. Credential harvesting (/etc/passwd, SSH keys, browser stores)\n-490 \n 491 ### Prerequisites\n 492 ```bash\n 493 source /opt/venv/bin/activate\n 494 pip -V  # Should show Python 3.12\n 495 ```\n 496 \n 497 ### Best Practices\n-498 - **Pre-install scan:** Always scan skills from unknown sources\n-499 - **Periodic audits:** Monthly security checks of installed skills\n-500 - **CI/CD integration:** Use `--format json` for automated security gates\n-501 - **Test file exclusions:** Scanner automatically whitelists test files (test_*.py, conftest.py)\n-502 - **Lock file exclusions:** NPM/pnpm/yarn/composer/poetry/Cargo/Gemfile lock files automatically skipped\n+524 - Always scan skills from unknown sources before installation\n+525 - Monthly security audits of installed skills (113 in repo)\n+526 - Use `--format json` for CI/CD automated security gates\n+527 - `--export-for-llm` for manual review when scanner needs human judgment\n 503 \n 504 ### Reference Documentation\n-505 - **SKILL.md:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/trustskill/SKILL.md` - Full documentation\n+530 - **SKILL.md:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/trustskill/SKILL.md`\n 506 - **Security Patterns:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/trustskill/references/security_patterns.md`\n-507 - **Test Reports:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/trustskill/security_scan_results/` - Historical scans\n+532 - **Test Reports:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/trustskill/security_scan_results/`\n 508 \n 509 ---\n 510 \n-511 *Updated: 2026-02-22*\n+536 *Updated: 2026-03-13 (validated against actual codebase)*","firstChangedLine":418},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773360619386}}
