{"type":"message","id":"2bed98bf","parentId":"f1540064","timestamp":"2026-03-13T00:34:36.475Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-13 08:34 GMT+8] please check whether your validated understanding of 'trustskill' is aligned with the following observations: ✦ After a meticulous review of the trustskill/ sub-folder, I have validated a deep understanding of the tool's architecture and functionality. My findings confirm that your summary of TrustSkill v3.1 is exceptionally accurate and aligns\n perfectly with the codebase.\n\n\n 🛡 Validated Deep Understanding vs. Your Summary\n\n\n\n ┌──────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬────────────┐\n │ Aspect │ My \"Validated\" Understanding │ Your Understanding │ Comparison │\n ├──────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────┤\n │ WHAT │ Advanced security scanner for OpenClaw skills using static analysis (Regex, AST, Taint). │ Advanced security scanner / \"antivirus\" for the OpenClaw skill ecosystem. │ Identical │\n │ WHY │ Security gate for installation, audits, and CI/CD integration (Exit Code 1 for HIGH risk). │ Pre-installation gate, audits, pre-execution, and publishing validation. │ Identical │\n │ HOW (Layers) │ 5 Layers: Regex, AST, Secret (Entropy 4.5+), Dependency (OSV), Taint (Source-to-Sink). │ Multi-layered detection: Regex, AST, Secret, Dependency, Taint. │ Identical │\n │ HOW (Modes) │ FAST (Regex/Secrets/Deps), STANDARD (+AST), DEEP (+Taint). │ FAST, STANDARD, DEEP modes with corresponding finding counts. │ Identical │\n │ v3.1 Tech │ NPM Integrity Hash Whitelist, Smart Data Flow (Upload/Download), i18n placeholders. │ 99% FP reduction, Smart Data Flow, Context-Aware Docs, i18n support. │ Identical │\n └──────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┴────────────┘\n\n\n\n 🔍 Key Codebase Confirmations\n * False Positive Reduction (v3.1): I verified in src/rules.py and src/analyzers/secret_analyzer.py that integrity hashes (sha512-xxx) in package-lock.json and yarn.lock are explicitly whitelisted, achieving the claimed 99% FP\n reduction.\n * Smart Data Flow: I confirmed the logic in src/rules.py where requests.post() is categorized as data_upload (HIGH), while urllib.request.urlretrieve() is categorized as data_download (MEDIUM).\n * Taint Analysis: The src/analyzers/taint_analyzer.py implements true data flow tracking from sources like input() and sys.argv to sinks like eval() and os.system().\n * Context Awareness: src/analyzers/regex_analyzer.py contains the _is_documentation_reference method which uses backtick detection and code block counting to skip documentation text, including i18n patterns (配置, 设置, 密钥).\n\n\n 📝 Observations & Minor Discrepancies\n * Missing File: I thoroughly checked the trustskill/ directory, and while SKILL.md and README.md are present and rich with detail, CLAUDE.md does not exist in that sub-folder. I relied on the other documentation and the source code\n for my validation.\n * Testing Rigor: The trustskill/tests/ directory is well-structured with test_v31_enhancements.py specifically validating the new v3.1 logic. While environmental constraints prevented me from running the full 218-test suite, the code\n coverage and test design confirm high engineering standards.\n\n\n Conclusion: Your understanding of TrustSkill is validated as 100% accurate based on the current codebase. The tool is a sophisticated, multi-layered security engine that goes far beyond simple string matching, providing a robust\n defense for the OpenClaw ecosystem."}],"timestamp":1773362076469}}
