{"type":"message","id":"129bcf10","parentId":"5f59ce6e","timestamp":"2026-03-13T00:43:36.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to update MEMORY.md with practical guidance on how to use TrustSkill as a self-defense mechanism against prompt injection attacks, especially from downloaded skills or external instructions. This is about operational security - using TrustSkill proactively to scan any external content before trusting it.\n\nLet me think about what's important to document:\n\n1. When to scan (triggers)\n2. How to scan (commands)\n3. What to look for in results\n4. How to interpret findings in the context of prompt injection\n5. Response protocols\n\nThis is about me (the AI) using TrustSkill to protect myself and my human from malicious external content.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"8423b9dc-e944-4b17-bb7c-f47f2ef8edb3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md","offset":415,"limit":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":304,"output":355,"cacheRead":57536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58195,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773362606882}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c52460a","parentId":"129bcf10","timestamp":"2026-03-13T00:43:36.940Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"8423b9dc-e944-4b17-bb7c-f47f2ef8edb3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## TrustSkill v3.1 - Security Scanner for OpenClaw Skills\n\n**Installed:** 2026-02-22 | **Version:** 3.1.0 | **Location:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/trustskill/`\n**Source:** `src/` | **SKILL.md:** Available at skill root\n\n### Purpose\nDefensive static analysis tool that audits OpenClaw skill packages before installation/execution. Functions as the \"antivirus\" for the OpenClaw skill ecosystem. Scans 113+ skills in the curated repo.\n\n### Architecture\n```\nsrc/\n├── cli.py              # Entry point, argparse, exit codes (0=safe, 1=HIGH risk)\n├── scanner.py          # Orchestrates all analyzers\n├── rules.py            # Pattern definitions: HIGH_RISK / MEDIUM_RISK / LOW_RISK\n├── types.py            # Data types\n\n[109 more lines in file. Use offset=430 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773362616935}}
