scripts/daily-ping-cron.sh`\n-232 - Logs: `/home/project/openclaw/logs/daily-ping-YYYY-MM-DD.log`\n+241 **Implementation (3 scripts):**\n+242 1. `/home/project/openclaw/run-daily-ping.sh` — Wrapper, runs steps 2+3\n+243 2. `/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh` — Fetches Bitcoin + stocks via yfinance\n+244 3. `/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-sender.py` — Parses logs, fetches GitHub trending, formats, sends via `openclaw message send`\n 233 \n+246 **Why system cron instead of agentTurn:**\n+247 - AgentTurn spawned an LLM session (30-60s overhead) just to run scripts\n+248 - yfinance delays caused frequent 5-minute timeout failures\n+249 - System cron runs in ~30 seconds total, no model dependency, no timeouts\n+250 \n+251 **Manual trigger:** `bash /home/project/openclaw/run-daily-ping.sh`\n+252 \n 234 **Known issues learned:**\n 235 - Gateway auth tokens can become stale in systemd after config updates\n 236 - Requires `daemon-reload` + full restart (not just `restart`)\n-237 - Cron job spawning timeout increased from 5 min → 15 min for yfinance delays\n-238 - Manual trigger: Use job UUID, not name\n+256 - Old agentTurn cron had timeout issues with yfinance (resolved by migrating to system cron)\n 239 \n 240 ---\n 241 \n 242 ## Infrastructure Notes\n     ...","firstChangedLine":209},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773367352842}}
