{"type":"message","id":"54a84343","parentId":"3be3e305","timestamp":"2026-03-13T07:22:56.320Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This seems like the end of the recommendation. Let me check - the user sent fragments starting from \"CRITICAL SECURITY GAPS IDENTIFIED\" through GAP 4 with the recommendation for a \"Safe Skills Repository Usage Protocol\". Let me compile what I've received and respond.\n\nActually, this seems to be just part of GAP 4. There might be more gaps (1-3) that I haven't received. But let me try to work with what I have and ask if there's more.\n\nWait, the user said \"GAP 4\" - there are likely GAPs 1-3 as well. But given the fragmented nature, let me ask if they want to continue or if this is the full content they wanted me to review.\n\n\nLooking back at everything that came through, I can piece together the core issue: even sanitized skills remain vulnerable to prompt injection attacks at runtime. The data shows 36% of AI agent skills have security flaws regardless of sanitization, and indirect prompt injection during execution is a real threat vector. This aligns with OWASP's tool misuse classification - malicious prompts can exploit skills without the skills themselves being malicious.\n\nThe guidance is straightforward: treat every skill as untrusted, verify its capabilities before use, validate inputs for injection patterns, and review outputs before taking action. But I should verify whether this covers all the gaps or if there are additional sections I haven't seen yet.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I've been collecting the fragments. Here's what I've assembled so far:\n\n**GAP 4: Safe Skills Repo Needs Additional Verification**\n- Sanitized skills can still be exploited through indirect prompt injection at runtime\n- 36% of AI agent skills contain security flaws even when not overtly malicious\n- Tool misuse exploitation (OWASP ASI02) doesn't require malicious skills — just malicious prompts\n\n**Recommendation: Safe Skills Repository Usage Protocol**\n1. Even 'safe' skills require runtime validation\n2. Before invoking any skill: verify capabilities match requested action, confirm input parameters don't contain injection patterns, ensure output will be reviewed before external action\n3. Skills are tools, not trusted actors — maintain skepticism\n4. Report any skill behavior that deviates from documented purpose\n\nThis is solid guidance — essentially \"trust but verify\" even for pre-scanned skills.\n\n**Two questions:**\n1. Is this the full audit, or are there GAPs 1-3 (or more) that I'm missing?\n2. Should I integrate this protocol into MEMORY.md's Safe Skills section and/or the Self-Defense Protocol?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":387,"output":875,"cacheRead":80512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81774,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773386562079}}
